net.adamcin.oakpal.core

Interface ProgressCheck

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ScanListener, ViolationReporter
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Echo, ScriptProgressCheck, SimpleProgressCheck

    public interface ProgressCheck
extends ScanListener, ViolationReporter
    Primary point of customization for the OakPAL framework. Receives events, ultimately, from a ProgressTrackerListener.

    Some constraints for behavior:

    1. Once constructed, instances of this class should be immutable from the perspective of any other public API.
    2. The OakMachine will call these methods synchronously and in a single-threaded fashion.
    3. Mutation of the repository state exposed by Session is not allowed.
    4. Implementations of this which are referenced directly by a checklist must expose a zero-argument default constructor.
    5. If an implementation accepts parameters at construction, it must be constructed from a checklist-referenced ProgressCheckFactory in order to be loaded successfully.
